requirement for it is described in brief here. a foreign national, who was eligible to become citizen of india on 26th january 1950 or belonged to a territory that became part of india after 15th august 1947 and his/her children and grand children are eligible for registration as oci. however, if the applicant had been a citizen of pakistan or bangladesh, he/she will not be eligible for oci. an oci registration card will be issued by the indian missions/posts abroad after scrutinizing the application and deciding eligibility. application forms along with other requirements such as photos, proof of eligibility, etc. 